[Kei-chan's book is here] amazon (https://amzn.asia/d/7NZwpPF) Rakuten books (https://books.rakuten.co.jp/rb/180366...)

[Follow] Ryosuke Instagram â†’ https://www.instagram.com/ryosuke.bucketlist/ Ryosuke Twitter â†’ https://twitter.com/ryosukeexitjac1

[Book publication decided]
https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4046053720

[Ryosuke's official website]
http://bucketlist-blog.com

[Kei-chan's channel is here]
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC1P6fv0uCNNTBQIWlhUVvaw

A channel that travels around the world with the theme of "THE BUCKET LIST (Things I want to do before I die)". A modern pirate and adventurer who travels around the world based overseas.

[Ryosuke's biography]
-Started his own business at age 25 (later became president of two companies)
-Purchased a huge camper at age 26
-10 million yen in debt at age 28
-Homeless for a year
-190,000 subscribers on YouTube in one year
-Wandered through 70 countries around the world
-Hitchhiked and slept outdoors from Spain to Russia
-Traveled across the US (over 17,000km in total)
-Traveled across Central America (Mexico to Panama)
-Traveled across South America (Colombia to Brazil)
-Working for charity around the world (on all continents)
-Established a fund to provide education to the world
-Started a business that supports employment around the world
-Interacted with tribes around the world
-Completed a triathlon
-Successfully summited a 6,100m mountain in Bolivia
-Started a home-based English study abroad service
-Opened a restaurant in Okinawa
-Owned a lodging facility in Okinawa
-Completed a 250km adventure race in the Sahara Desert
-Aconcagua (7,000m), the highest peak in South America

GIRLS BAND CRY
[Introduction]
The main character drops out of high school in her second year, and aims at entering a university while working alone in Tokyo.
A girl is betrayed by her friends and doesn't know what to do.
Another girl is abandoned by her parents, and tries to survive in the city by doing part-time jobs.
This world lets us down all the time.
Nothing goes as planned.
But we want something that we can continue to like.
We believe there's a place where we belong. That's why we sing.

[Staff]

GIRLS BAND CRY
[Introduction]
The main character drops out of high school in her second year, and aims at entering a university while working alone in Tokyo.
A girl is betrayed by her friends and doesn't know what to do.
Another girl is abandoned by her parents, and tries to survive in the city by doing part-time jobs.
This world lets us down all the time.
Nothing goes as planned.
But we want something that we can continue to like.
We believe there's a place where we belong. That's why we sing.

en-US.title: [1 million subscribers anniversary] Three chefs celebrated by preparing meals
en-US.description:
Thank you so much for reaching 1 million subscribers!
This time, we have a special episode with my old friends, Chef Kawagoe and Chef Masutani, who I've known for 25 years!

â†“Click here to subscribe to the "Narrow Road to Cooking" channelâ†“â€»Scheduled to be released every Wednesday and Saturday from 19:00
http://www.youtube.com/@sanpiryoron?sub_confirmation=1

YouTube "It's Chef Kawagoe."
https://www.youtube.com/@kawagoechef_dayo

YouTube "Masutani's Simple is best"
https://www.youtube.com/@user-fp3kr9um6b

Chef Kawagoe
â– Pork kimchi cheese sauce (serves 3-4)

[Ingredients]
150g pork shoulder loin, 150g pork belly, 300g kimchi, 1/2 new onion, 1/2 pack of enoki mushrooms, 1 pack of watercress, 20g fresh cream, 1-2 tablespoons olive oil, appropriate amount of cottage cheese

A â€»Cheese sauce (4 tablespoons mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons mascarpone, grated garlic 1/2 teaspoon of soy sauce, a pinch of salt, 1-2 tablespoons of grated cheese)

B *Pork seasoning (2 tablespoons of sesame oil, 1 tablespoon of potato starch, a pinch of salt)

C *Kimchi seasoning (1 teaspoon of oyster sauce, 1 teaspoon of gochujang, 1 teaspoon of sweet bean paste)

[How to make]
â‘  Whisk the cream until it is 5-8 minutes thick.
â‘¡ Thinly slice the spring onions.
Cut the enoki mushrooms in half and break them up.
â‘¢ Separate the watercress into leaves and stems.
Roughly chop the stems.
â‘£ Mix A well.
Add the whipped cream and mix lightly.
â‘¤ Cut the pork shoulder and pork belly into bite-sized pieces and sprinkle with B.
â‘¥ Mix the kimchi with C. â‘¦ Add olive oil (1-2 tablespoons) to a frying pan, add the spring onions and enoki mushrooms, sprinkle with a pinch of salt, and fry over medium heat.
â‘§ Once soft, add the watercress stalks, stir fry briefly, then remove.
â‘¨ Add the pork to the same frying pan and stir fry over high-medium heat. Once almost cooked through, add the kimchi and the vegetables that were set aside, and stir fry briefly.
â‘© Serve in a bowl, sprinkle with cottage cheese, garnish with the watercress leaves, top with the cheese sauce from â‘£, and finish by drizzling with olive oil.

Chef Masutani
â– Spaghetti with shrimp, mushrooms and shiso leaves (serves 2)

[Ingredients]
200g spaghetti, 130g peeled shrimp, 1 pack of shimeji mushrooms, 10 shiso leaves, 2 cloves of garlic, 1 chili pepper, 2 tablespoons of olive oil, 1 tablespoon of sake, 1 teaspoon of white sesame seeds, 1.5 tablespoons of concentrated simple dashi (white dashi or noodle soup can also be used), 10g of rock salt per liter, salt to taste

[How to make]
â‘  Add rock salt (10g) to 1 liter of hot water
Prepare hot water with a salt concentration of 1%.
â‘¡ Remove the vein from the peeled shrimp
Mix with salt and wash with water.
â‘¢ Thinly slice the garlic.
Remove the stems of the shimeji mushrooms and separate them.
Finely chop the shiso leaves.
â‘£ Add olive oil (2 tablespoons) to a frying pan

Add sliced â€‹â€‹garlic and one chili pepper.

*Mash the chili pepper and add the seeds as well.

â‘¤ Boil the spaghetti in the water from â‘  for 30 seconds.

â‘¥ Heat the oil from â‘£ over low heat for about 1 minute to bring out the aroma

Add the peeled shrimp and stir fry lightly.

â‘¦ Add sake (1 tablespoon)

Add shimeji mushrooms and stir fry over medium heat until soft.

â‘§ Add white sesame seeds (1 teaspoon)

Add concentrated simple dashi (1.5 tablespoons)

Bring to a boil.

*You can also use white dashi or noodle soup for the concentrated simple dashi.

â‘¨ Add the boiled pasta and shiso leaves.

Turn off the heat and mix.

â‘© Serve in a bowl and finish by pouring olive oil over it.

Masahiro Kasahara
â– Curry Chinese rice bowl (serves 3-4)

Ingredients: 200g sliced â€‹â€‹pork belly, 1/4 Chinese cabbage, 1/2 carrot, 4 shiitake mushrooms, 1/2 onion, 1 pack bean sprouts, 5 crab sticks, 10 boiled quail eggs, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1.5 tablespoons curry powder, 3 tablespoons water-dissolved potato starch, a little salt, a little pepper, rice (as needed)

A (600cc dashi (water is also acceptable, 50cc soy sauce, 50cc mirin)

B (1 tablespoon sugar, 1 tablespoon vinegar)

How to make: â‘  Cut the Chinese cabbage into white and green parts.
ã€€ Roughly chop the green parts.
ã€€ Slice the white parts into thin slices.

â‘¡ Wash the carrots, skin on, and cut them into thin chrysanthemum shapes.
Cut off only the tough parts of the stems of the shiitake mushrooms

and tear them into small pieces with your hands.

Thinly slice the onion.

Wash and roughly chop the bean sprouts.

Tear the crab sticks apart with your hands.

â‘¢ Cut the pork into 5cm lengths.

â‘£ Add olive oil (1 tbsp) to a frying pan

Add the pork, season with salt and pepper, and fry over medium heat.

Once the meat is cooked, add the vegetables except the bean sprouts

Sprinkle with a little salt

Add a little dashi (water is fine too)

Heat until the vegetables are soft.

â‘¤ Add curry powder (1.5 tbsp)

Stir-fry until fragrant.

Add A, bean sprouts, and crab sticks, and simmer lightly. â‘¥ Add B and season with salt and pepper.

en.title: The Bright and Dark Sides of the Happiest Country: Finland
en.description:
In today's video, I travel to Finland, known as the happiest country in the world, to experience the reality of life firsthand. While Finland is often praised for its high quality of life, I take a deeper look into what truly lies behind its reputation. From its strong economy and high tax rates to its world-renowned education system and social security, I explore how these factors impact people's everyday lives.
I meet locals to hear about the reality of life in Finland, including the challenges they face. One growing concern is mental health issues, which have been increasing despite Finlandâ€™s global happiness ranking. I also take a look at Finlandâ€™s approach to homelessness and how the country supports those in need. Along the way, I experience Finnish food and culture.
Join me as I uncover the reality of life in Finland, beyond the headlines. If you enjoy travel vlogs, donâ€™t forget to like, comment, and subscribe!

nl.title: De lichte en donkere kanten van het gelukkigste land: Finland
nl.description:
In de video van vandaag reis ik naar Finland, bekend als het gelukkigste land ter wereld, om de realiteit van het leven met eigen ogen te zien. Hoewel Finland vaak wordt geprezen om zijn hoge levenskwaliteit, ga ik dieper in op wat er werkelijk achter zijn reputatie schuilgaat. Van zijn sterke economie en hoge belastingtarieven tot zijn wereldberoemde onderwijssysteem en sociale zekerheid, ik onderzoek hoe deze factoren het dagelijks leven van mensen beÃ¯nvloeden.
Ik ontmoet locals om te horen over de realiteit van het leven in Finland, inclusief de uitdagingen waarmee ze worden geconfronteerd. Een groeiende zorg zijn problemen met de geestelijke gezondheid, die toenemen ondanks de wereldwijde geluksranglijst van Finland. Ik kijk ook naar de Finse aanpak van dakloosheid en hoe het land mensen in nood ondersteunt. Onderweg ervaar ik Fins eten en cultuur.
Ga met me mee terwijl ik de realiteit van het leven in Finland ontdek, voorbij de krantenkoppen. Als je van reisvlogs houdt, vergeet dan niet te liken, commentaar te geven en je te abonneren!

es.description:
En el video de hoy viajo a Finlandia, conocido como el paÃ­s mÃ¡s feliz del mundo, para experimentar la realidad de la vida de primera mano. Si bien Finlandia suele ser elogiada por su alta calidad de vida, analizo en profundidad lo que realmente se esconde detrÃ¡s de su reputaciÃ³n. Desde su sÃ³lida economÃ­a y sus altas tasas impositivas hasta su sistema educativo y seguridad social de renombre mundial, exploro cÃ³mo estos factores afectan la vida cotidiana de las personas.
Conozco a los lugareÃ±os para escuchar sobre la realidad de la vida en Finlandia, incluidos los desafÃ­os que enfrentan. Una preocupaciÃ³n creciente son los problemas de salud mental, que han ido en aumento a pesar de la clasificaciÃ³n mundial de felicidad de Finlandia. TambiÃ©n analizo el enfoque de Finlandia sobre las personas sin hogar y cÃ³mo el paÃ­s apoya a los necesitados. En el camino, experimento la comida y la cultura finlandesas.

fil.title: Ang Maliwanag at Madilim na Gilid ng Pinakamasayang Bansa: Finland
fil.description:
Sa video ngayon, naglalakbay ako sa Finland, na kilala bilang ang pinakamasayang bansa sa mundo, para maranasan ang realidad ng buhay. Bagama't madalas na pinupuri ang Finland para sa mataas na kalidad ng buhay nito, mas malalim kong tinitingnan kung ano talaga ang nasa likod ng reputasyon nito. Mula sa malakas nitong ekonomiya at mataas na rate ng buwis hanggang sa kilalang sistema ng edukasyon at seguridad sa lipunan nito, tinutuklasan ko kung paano nakakaapekto ang mga salik na ito sa pang-araw-araw na buhay ng mga tao.
Nakikipagkita ako sa mga lokal upang marinig ang tungkol sa realidad ng buhay sa Finland, kabilang ang mga hamon na kinakaharap nila. Ang isang lumalaking alalahanin ay ang mga isyu sa kalusugan ng isip, na tumataas sa kabila ng pandaigdigang ranggo ng kaligayahan ng Finland. Tinitingnan ko rin ang diskarte ng Finland sa kawalan ng tirahan at kung paano sinusuportahan ng bansa ang mga nangangailangan. Sa daan, nararanasan ko ang Finnish na pagkain at kultura.
Samahan mo ako sa pagtuklas ko sa realidad ng buhay sa Finland, sa kabila ng mga headline. Kung natutuwa ka sa mga travel vlog, huwag kalimutang mag-like, magkomento, at mag-subscribe!

jv.title: Sisih Padhang lan Gelap Negara Paling Bahagia: Finlandia
jv.description:
Ing video dina iki, aku lelungan menyang Finlandia, sing dikenal minangka negara paling seneng ing donya, kanggo ngalami kasunyatan urip langsung. Nalika Finland asring dipuji amarga kualitas urip sing dhuwur, aku nliti luwih jero babagan apa sing ana ing mburi reputasi kasebut. Saka ekonomi sing kuwat lan tarif pajak sing dhuwur nganti sistem pendhidhikan lan keamanan sosial sing misuwur ing donya, aku njelajah kepiye pengaruh faktor kasebut ing urip saben dinane.
Aku ketemu wong lokal kanggo krungu bab kasunyatan urip ing Finland, kalebu tantangan padha ngadhepi. Salah sawijining keprihatinan sing saya tambah yaiku masalah kesehatan mental, sing saya tambah akeh sanajan peringkat kebahagiaan global Finlandia. Aku uga ndeleng pendekatan Finlandia kanggo ora duwe omah lan kepiye negara kasebut ndhukung wong sing butuh. Sadawane dalan, aku ngalami panganan lan budaya Finlandia.
Gabung karo aku nalika nemokake kasunyatan urip ing Finlandia, ngluwihi berita utama. Yen sampeyan seneng vlog perjalanan, aja lali like, komen, lan subscribe!

id.title: Sisi Cerah dan Gelap Negara Paling Bahagia: Finlandia
id.description:
Dalam video hari ini, saya bepergian ke Finlandia, yang dikenal sebagai negara paling bahagia di dunia, untuk merasakan realitas kehidupan secara langsung. Meskipun Finlandia sering dipuji karena kualitas hidupnya yang tinggi, saya akan mencermati lebih dalam apa yang sebenarnya ada di balik reputasinya. Dari ekonominya yang kuat dan tarif pajak yang tinggi hingga sistem pendidikan dan jaminan sosialnya yang terkenal di dunia, saya mengeksplorasi bagaimana faktor-faktor ini memengaruhi kehidupan sehari-hari masyarakat.
Saya bertemu dengan penduduk setempat untuk mendengar tentang realitas kehidupan di Finlandia, termasuk tantangan yang mereka hadapi. Salah satu masalah yang berkembang adalah masalah kesehatan mental, yang terus meningkat meskipun Finlandia berada di peringkat kebahagiaan global. Saya juga mencermati pendekatan Finlandia terhadap tunawisma dan bagaimana negara tersebut mendukung mereka yang membutuhkan. Sepanjang perjalanan, saya merasakan makanan dan budaya Finlandia.
Bergabunglah dengan saya saat saya mengungkap realitas kehidupan di Finlandia, di luar berita utama. Jika Anda menyukai vlog perjalanan, jangan lupa untuk menyukai, berkomentar, dan berlangganan! â–¶IG Antti (Band)

This video is a mix of OmeTV and Tokyo! Japanese polyglot spoke 15 languages and stunned people worldwide by speaking their native language! There are many particularly impressive encounters this time around. It's definitely one of my favorite videos!
Currently, I speak 14 languages, which I studied properly. These are English, Spanish, French, Portuguese, Arabic, Indonesian, Russian, Hindi, German, Turkish, Chinese, Thai, Korean, Polish and Dutch. And now I'm learning Greek, Tagalog, Cantonese, and Italian! Apart from that, I speak Japanese for sure, which is my native language.
Furthermore, I know a tiny bit of Italian, Swedish, Romanian, Farsi, Swahili, Tagalog, Burmese, Geogian, Finnish, Uzbek, Kazakh and Bengali!
Of course, my skills of these languages are still far from sufficient.
The thing I value the most, however, is the attitude to trying to know their culture.
Interacting with people from different background is an eye-opening experience and that makes me really happy.
I wanna inspire people to learn different languages.

snippet.title: MLB x Demon Slayer: Anime Movie (feat. Shohei Ohtani, Shota Imanaga, and more!)
snippet.description:
As MLB celebrates games in Japan, baseball has partnered to release a Demon Slayer short that depicts the evolution of Japanese baseball through the continuous passing of the torch across generations

Product around the collaboration will become available for order during the MLB Tokyo Series. Further details coming soon
